National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Bulgarian Prime Minister Kiril Petkov to discuss Russia's military aggression against Ukraine. They both expressed their support for Ukraine and their willingness to impose costs on Russia. Sullivan emphasized the US's solidarity with Bulgaria in the face of Russia's use of energy as a weapon. They also talked about efforts to diversify European energy supplies and Bulgaria's focus on rule of law and anti-corruption reforms. The importance of promoting stability and prosperity in the Western Balkans was also discussed.